      "@timmaxw maybe I'm wrong, but that doesn't seem right.\r\n\r\nAssume m is the mean, and n the number of samples (assuming population variance):\r\n```\r\nv = 1/n sum (x_i - m)^2\r\n  = 1/n sum [(x_i)^2 - 2mx_i + m^2]\r\n  = 1/n sum [(x_i)^2 - 2mx_i] + m^2\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhile if I'm not mistaken, your algorithm comes down to\r\n```\r\nv = 1/n [sum (x_i)^2] - m^2\r\n```\r\nwhich looks different."
